 In celebration of the 40th birthday of Pastor Leke Adeboye, the son of the revered General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), an empowerment scheme has been launched to train 40 youths in various digital skills. Adeboye doubles as the Principal Executive Assistant to the General Overseer of RCCG and Assistant Pastor-in-Charge of Province (CSR), RCCG Youth Province 1. The training will be held between June and August 2022 at the Redemption Camp. This initiative, according to Adebayo, is one of the numerous programmes and projects designed to give hope to many Nigerian youths in celebration of Pastor Leke’s 40th birthday. The training will cover in-depth training in Data Science. The training will be held in partnership with the IncubatorNg and other stakeholders. It is for people intending to pivot into a career in tech or those willing to upgrade their skills. Adeboye, in a press statement, explained that he is organising the digital skills training to help many young Nigerians transition into tech and prepare for the future of work and increase Africa’s tech talent base. Born on 20 May 1982 into the family of Pastors Enoch and Folu Adeboye, his 40th birthday was celebrated across the world by families, friends and senior clerics in RCCG on 20th of May 2022. As a leader, who believes in the greatness of Nigeria and her youths, he highlighted that the training will go a long way in helping young Nigerians find their footing in the emerging global tech economy and the future of work. According to the celebrant, his goal is to see that beneficiaries of the empowerment training go on to work with global tech giants as well as found their own tech organisations.Attachments area